      interactiveElement: `Draw a "barriers web" diagram: place "Poverty Trap" in the centre and draw arrows connecting it to six surrounding barriers — Infrastructure Deficit, Weak Institutions, Corruption, Geography/Disease Burden, Commodity Dependence, and Capital Flight. For each link, write one sentence explaining the causal mechanism. Then identify which two barriers you believe are most fundamental and justify your reasoning. This exercise helps IB students organise multi-cause arguments for Paper 1 essays.`,
