        front: 'Distinguish between "tied aid" and "untied aid" and explain why tied aid is often criticised.',
        back: 'Tied aid requires the recipient country to spend the aid on goods and services from the donor country. Untied aid allows recipients to procure from the most competitive source. Tied aid is criticised because: (1) it often means purchasing overpriced donor-country goods; (2) it restricts recipient ownership and policy space; (3) the OECD estimates tied aid is 15–30% less efficient than untied aid because of procurement restrictions.',
